<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Envoy's Driver, Bodyguard Arrested in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The driver and the bodyguard of the
Russian president's envoy in Chechnya, who was kidnapped on the
border between Chechnya and Ingushetia Friday, have been arrested
by the Chechen police, the Itar-Tass news agency reported from
Grozny, capital of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
The Russian representative to Chechnya, Valentin Vlasov, on
President Boris Yeltsin's order, had attended to the Chechen
settlement in the previous government and in his former capacity
as Russian Security Council secretary, flew to Grozny Friday
evening, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Vlasov was abducted when he was traveling in the republic of
Ingushsetia, just a few kilometers from the border of the
breakaway Chechen Republic when he was kidnapped.
</P>
<P>
CIS Executive Secretary Boris Berezovsky regarded the
kidnapping of the commissioner of the Russian president in
Chechnya as a provocation.
</P>
<P>
"It was a thoroughly planned, absolutely political
provocation," Berezovsky said. He held that the event was linked
with the attack at a tank brigade in late December 1997.
</P>
<P>
"Neither Boris Yeltsin and his circle nor the Grozny
authorities, including Aslan Maskhadov, Shmil Basayev and Movladi
Udugov, are interested in the current developments and the
aggravated regional situation," Berezovsky noted.
</P>
<P>
Chechen minister of Shariah and state security Islam Khalimov
said, "The abduction is politically motivated and designed to
aggravate the tension in the region and in the relations between
Russia and Chechnya when a new Russian government is taking over."
</P>
<P>
Under the instruction of the president a group consisting of
Acting Vice-Premier Ivan Rybkin, deputy head of the Russian
Security Council General Boris Agapov and government commissioner
in Chechnya Georgy Kurin have left for Chechnya to investigate
the incident.
</P>
<P>
Chechen President Aslan Maskhadov has instructed all law
enforcement agencies to identify the organizers and perpetrators
of the crime and take steps to set Vlasov free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
