<HEADLINE> Annan Concerned at New Hostilities in Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 1 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan Friday expressed his deep concern over the recent severe
fighting between the Tajik government forces and elements of the
United Tajik Opposition (UTO).
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Mission of Observers in Tajikistan has
reported severe fighting east of Dushanbe and within the eastern
city limits, which began Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fighting was apparently triggered by the arrest of three
opposition members on criminal charges.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the secretary-general said he is very concerned
over the newly flared hostilities, which carries the risk of
escalation.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief called the Tajiki Government and the UTO to work
together to stop the fighting and to restore calm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
