<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Entrepreneurs Urged to Improve Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Friday urged entrepreneurs here to raise the salary and
improve the working condition of their employees.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a mass gathering marking the International Labor
Day today, Chissano said entrepreneurs should compete to see who
has best pay and working condition for the employees.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government has raised the minimum salary
three times in recent years, with the minimum pay per month from
27 U.S. Dollars raised to 30.5 Dollars for the civil servants.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Premier Pascoal Mocumbi said on the occasion that
the economy and the living standard of the Mozambican people have
been continuously improving after a series of economic and social
reform measures were taken by the government.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the local elections scheduled for June 30, he said
Mozambican citizens should vote in an organized, well-ordered,
and civilized manner this year as they did in the 1994 general
elections.
</P>
<P>
He promised that the government should do its best to
guarantee peace, stability and national unity so as to reduce
poverty and improve the living standard of the people.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 people including ministers and parliament
deputies attended the gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
