<DOCNO> XIE19980502.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Concerned About Conflict in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkey warned Friday that the Kosovo
conflict might threaten the security and stability of the Balkan
region if an immediate solution can't be found.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is closely following the latest developments in the
Yugoslav province with grave concern, a written statement issued
by Turkish Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the region would not be dragged into an
atmosphere of unconfidence and unstability as was experienced in
Bosnia-Herzegovina," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said Turkey welcomes international efforts made by the
six-nation Contact Group comprising the United States, Britain,
France, Germany, Italy and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the six countries held a meeting Wednesday in
Rome, Italy to discuss ways of easing tensions in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The statement, however, noted that the Kosovo issue should be
resolved within the framework of maintaining territorial
integrity of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a Yugoslav province with an ethnic Albanian
majority. Conflicts between Serb police and ethnic Albanian
protesters demanding independence from Serbia have reportedly
killed at least 80 people since February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
