<HEADLINE> Kampala Sprays Drugs to Kill Nairobi Fly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Kampala City Council (KCC) has
started spraying drugs in the most affected areas in Kampala and
its neighboring areas to kill Nairobi fly.
</P>
<P>
The insect number was increasing and so KCC launched the
spraying operation in Kampala and Mpigi District, the daily
newspaper Monitor Friday quoted Herbert Semakula, KCC's public
relations official, as saying.
</P>
<P>
The spraying is underway in Mekerere University, Kololo, old
Kampala, Mbuya, Nakasero and Muyenga Divisions in the capital
city and Makindye, Kawempe, Nateete and Nalukologo in Mpigi
District bordering Kampala, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Nairobi fly is propagated in areas covered by substantial
plants under warm and rainy conditions.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, the insect never bites people but it
spreads a kind of poisonous substance which causes pain and
swelling in human skin. It bothers patients in a period of some
two weeks and poses no danger to its victims.
</P>
<P>
The drugs used in Kampala also kill flies, mosquitos and other
harmful insects, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
