to us. But because we are sick, we have no choice but to go to
Washington and ask for a cure," he said.
</P>
<P>
President Mkapa also reiterated the government's determination
to privatize the parastatals, saying that in most cases the
government failed to run them well.
</P>
<P>
"In order to save our industries and our economy, the
government will continue to encourage foreign investors to come
and invest in different sectors," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa stressed the importance of cracking down on the
corruption of government officials, calling all his people to
fight against them by revealing their names.
</P>
<P>
"We leave our culprits stealing large sum of public funds
allocated for national development projects, but we take up the
law in our hands in stoning to death young boys suspected of
stealing 1,000 (Tanzanian) Shillings," he said.  
