<HEADLINE> Ethiopia: Minister Urges Employers, Workers to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of Labour
and Social Affairs Hassen Abdella Friday urged the employers and
workers in the country to resolve their misunderstandings through
dialog and negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the call when he was addressing a meeting
here organized by the Confederation of Ethiopian Trade Unions to
mark the Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
Hassen stressed the need for healthy worker-employer
relationship.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the minister as saying that
workers should exercise prudence not to sever their relations
with employers in utilizing their rights to organize, negotiate
and voice discontentments.
</P>
<P>
The actions of some employers constitute a threat to the lives
of workers, Vice-President of the confederation Zenebe Kebede was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Zenebe said that workers should have a say in the recently
announced government's plan to privatize 115 development projects
worth close to 40 billion Birr (5.7 billion U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to reports, eight labour union federations under the
confederation also used the occasion to call for workers'
participation in structural adjustment and privatization
programs.
</P>
<P>
May day, the International Labour Day, is celebrated for the
23rd time in Ethiopia this year. 
