the Ingushetian village of Assinovskaya, close to the Chechnya
border early Friday, which makes this the first abduction of a
senior Russian official.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Kazbek Makhashev, who runs Chechnya's
security forces, and other Chechen officials vowed to work closely
together on the rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
