<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Long March Rocket Ideal for Commercial Launches," Says Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Long March 2C rocket is
capable of competing in the international market for commercial
launches of medium- and low-orbit satellites, an official of the
China Great Wall Industry Corp. said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview at the Taiyuan Satellite Launch Center in north
China's Shanxi Province, Liu Zhixiong, vice-president of China
Great Wall, said that the capability of the Long March 2C has been
proved in three launches of Iridium satellites in succession.
</P>
<P>
At 17:16 pm (Beijing Time), a Long March 2C rocket lifted off
from the launch center here and successfully carried into
preset orbits two Iridium satellites made by the Motorola
Corporation of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Liu said the improved version of the Long March 2C rocket was
manufactured in line with the requirements of Motorola for the
task of launching Iridium satellites; it is made up of two
sub-stages and a newly-made satellite distributor.
</P>
<P>
Compared with ther Long March 2C rocket, the improved Long
March 2C carrier rocket has adopted more new technology, including
the 3.35-m-diameter fairing of the improved Long March 3A rocket,
an extra-long two-stage storage container for fuel and oxidizing
agent, and two-stage jet-pipe engines.
</P>
<P>
The rocket is about 40 m in length and its lifting-off
weight is 213 tons. It can carry two Iridium satellites into
preset orbits with one launch.
</P>
<P>
On the international market for the commercial launching of
medium- and low-orbit satellites, Liu said that in the coming
decade there will be a boom in the launching of such satellites,
adding that the number will reach more than 700.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the potential market for such launches
offers opportunities and challenges for Long March rockets.
</P>
<P>
The improved version of the Long March 2C rocket was first
launched on September 1, 1997. On December 8 last year and March
26 this year, the rocket respectively carried two Iridium
satellites into orbit.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that 1998 will be a busy year for the Long March
2C rocket, as it is expected to undergo three or four launches.
</P>
<P>
According to the preliminary agreement between China Great Wall
and Motorola, the next launch of an Iridium satellite will be in
July this year, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
China Great Wall will carry out four or five launches for
Motorola before the Iridium satellite network goes into operation
and six or more launches for the maintenance of the network in the
next few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980502.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Parliament Backs 11-Nation Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Parliament in a
pre-summit session approved a recommendation by the European
Commission that Belgium, Germany, France, Spain, Italy, Ireland,
Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Austria, Portugal and Finland be the
first member countries to adopt the single euro currency.
</P>
<P>
The European legislators voted 467 for, 65 against, with 24
abstentions, in favor of the recommendation made by the commission
on March 25.
</P>
<P>
The vote follows a recommendation from EU finance ministers on
Friday, when the EU finance ministers judged these countries to be
in good enough economic shape to switch to the euro on January 1
and start shedding their national currencies.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the 15 EU leaders are close to a deal on who will
run the European central bank. The bank job will go to Wim
Duisenberg, 62, an ex-Dutch central bank chief. Under a
compromise taking shape, he will not serve a full eight-year term,
but at some point he will step aside in favor of Jean-Claude
Trichet, 55, the French central bank governor.
</P>
<P>
For now, Britain, Sweden and Denmark opt to stay out, while
Greece does not meet the entry criteria, such as low inflation and
interest rates and small budget deficits.
</P>
<P>
European heads of state and government are holding a summit
meeting now to give the final go-ahead for the single currency to
be formally launched. 
</P>
</TEXT>
