<HEADLINE> Public Tours of HK's New Airport Prior to Opening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 90,000 people will tour
the passenger terminal at the new Hong Kong International Airport
through a series of open days in May and June prior to its opening
scheduled for July 6, the Airport Authority (AA) announced
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The "The New Airport Experience" program aims to familiarize
Hong Kong people with their new airport, AA Corporate Development
Director Clinton Leeks told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"The amount of public interest over the seven years of the
Airport Core Program has been phenomenal," Leeks said. "The
program of open days will be educational as well as entertaining,
and a fitting salute to the world's largest infrastructure
project."
</P>
<P>
General Manager Corporate Co-ordination Dora Kay, responsible
for co-ordination of the AA's pre-opening events, told the press
conference that the program takes in the new road transportation
network to and from the new airport as well as facilities within
the airport itself.
</P>
<P>
On fully guided tours within the passenger terminal, people
will learn more about its features as they go through the entire
passenger handling process, she said.
</P>
<P>
AA is organizing the program in conjunction with the Community
Chest, bus companies, Hong Kong Sky Mall retailers and airlines.
</P>
