<HEADLINE> South Korean Dance Troope Arrives in DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- A South Korean dance troupe
composed of students arrived in Pyongyang Saturday afternoon,
marking the first cultural contact between the two sides in more
than a decade.
</P>
<P>
The 64-member troupe received a warm welcome after they landed
at the Pyongyang airport, the Central News Agency of the DPRK
reported.
</P>
<P>
Headed by Pak Bo-hui, chairman of the Global Peace Association
of South Korea, the Little Angels troupe will stage three
performances in the DPRK capital during its 11-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The Korean peninsula conducted the first cultural exchange in
September 1985 after 40 years of separation when Pyongyang and
Seoul sent dancing troupes to visit each other.
</P>
<P>
This time, South Korea will also invite a dancing group of DPRK
pupils to perform in Seoul. 
