<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing said the
Chinese government believes that China's modernization drive
depends on education, and education must serve the country's
modernization.
</P>
<P>
The government has given top priority to the growth of science
and education, and has worked out a strategy of "revitalizing the
nation by developing science and education", he said.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by the vice-premier, who is also a member
of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee's, at today's opening of
"the University of the 21st Century", a forum held in conjunction
with the celebrations for the centennial of Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of more than 60 foreign universities and over 30
domestic ones attended the two-day forum to discuss the growth of
higher education in the 21st century, the status and role of
universities, and other related topics.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the forum, the vice-premier said that China is a
developing country and its modernization drive will take a long
time, so the country's higher education circles should not neglect
this reality.
</P>
<P>
Scientists and other professional people are the core of higher
education, Li said, noting that higher education plays a very
important role connecting tradition and reality, the past and the
future, the natural sciences and the social sciences, theory and
experience, and individuals and society.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, China now has more than 1,000 universities and
over 1,000 higher educational institutions for adults, with more
than six million students. He expressed his hope that in the next
century a number of Chinese universities will become world leaders.
</P>
<P>
He termed the participation of foreign university presidents in
Beijing University's centennial celebrations a "special glory" for
the school.
</P>
<P>
Modern universities appeared in China only about 100 years ago,
according to the vice-premier. He said Beijing University is the
one of oldest universities in China, and that it has made
important contributions to promoting academic and social progress
in the country.  
</P>
