<HEADLINE> Senior Hong Kong Citizens Commended for Good Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen senior Hong Kong citizens
were commended for their outstanding performance in motor ability
tests at the closing ceremony of the "Recreation and Sports
Fortnight for Older Persons" held at the Hong Kong Park Indoor
Games Hall here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
As a program of the event, the motor ability tests were aimed
at examining such general health factors of the elderly as weight,
height and blood pressure. The tests were also used to assess
their strength, power of balance, eye-hand co-ordination and
agility.
</P>
<P>
To promote its "Sports-for-all" concept among senior citizens,
Hong Kong's Provisional Urban Council has staged more than 100
events including motor ability tests, a video demonstration of
healthy exercises at the centers for the elderly, health talks and
sports, attracting more than 20,000 participants.
</P>
<P>
The limelights at Saturday's ceremony were the awarding of the
grand prize to two most senior citizens -- Leung Heep-yuan, 87,
and Ip Tin, 92.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was followed by social dance performances and a
healthy exercise demonstration by the senior citizens, as well as
play-in sessions of gateball, indoor lawn bowls, taiji boxing and
fitness exercises. 
