the List Voting System works" as the first Legislative Council
Election of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
draws near.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure openness and fairness of the first HKSAR LegCo
Election, the government has set up the interactive telephone
hotline through which the public can have easy access to the free
phone service telling them what the List Voting System is before
they cast their vote," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The phone message lasts about two and a half minutes and
callers may simply press the button to listen to the language of
their choice. If callers have further questions on the LegCo
Election, they may call the election hotline on 2588-1212. The
telephone is manned by the staff members of the Registration and
Electoral Office. 
