<HEADLINE> Urgent: China Launches Two US-Made Satellites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 2 (Xinhua) -- China has successfully sent two
US-made Iridium satellites into orbit from the Taiyuan Satellite
Launch Center in north China's Shanxi Province late this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
It is the third time that a China-made Long March rocket
carried into space two Iridium satellites made by the US-based
Motorola Corporation.  
</P>
