<HEADLINE> Wong Kam Po Wins 15th Stage of Philippine Cycling Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Wong Kam Po from Hong Kong, China,
won the 15th stage of the Tour of the Philippines on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Wong, the defending champion, came in just one bike's length
before three Filipinos, Nilo Estayo, Manuel Mendoza and Michael
Gonowan who crossed the finish line virtually simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
The stage covered 165 kilometer race from the northern town of
Agoo in La Union province to the Clark Economic Zone, a former
American airbase.
</P>
<P>
Warren Davadilla of the Philippines continued to lead the
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
His compatriots Carlo Guieb, Victor Espiritu and Santy
Barnaches remained at the second, third and fourth places
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The final stage is a 80-kilometer race to Manila on Sunday.
</P>
