<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo Port Becomes Major Container Shipping Outlet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo Port in east China's
Zhejiang Province has developed into one of the largest container
shipping ports in the country in recent years thanks to extensive
efforts to offer improved services to attract clients.
</P>
<P>
First quarter figures show the port handled 78,500 TEU
containers, up 40 percent on last year's period. The port
handled a total of 250,000 TEU containers in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The port, constructed in the early 1980s, was formerly a major
transit port linking the international and domestic
markets. Ningbo Port was transformed into one of the nation's
largest container docks in the early 1990s, and has since served
as a transit port for containers destined for Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Local port authorities have placed priority on improving port
facilities and services for container shipping.
</P>
<P>
The port has introduced ocean-going shipping services in recent
years in cooperation with various domestic and international
shipping companies.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo Port has opened three regular container shipping routes
to ports in Europe and the Americas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
