<HEADLINE> Kazakh Foreign Minister on Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- As their relations expand rapidly,
Kazakhstan and China in recent years have deepened cooperation in
all areas, said Kazakh Foreign Minister Kasymzhomart Tokayev.
</P>
<P>
The advance of the Kazakh-Chinese relations -- political,
economic and trade -- has been smooth as it is blessed by leaders
of both countries, Tokayev told Xinhua in a recent interview.
</P>
<P>
The two sides entered into a new era of bilateral economic
cooperation last September with the signing of an agreement to
work more closely in the oil sector, he said.
</P>
<P>
That accord was forged during then Chinese Premier Li Peng and
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing's visit to Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
As a latest development, the foreign minister said, extensive
preparation work for Kazakh Prime Minister Nurlan Balgimbaev's
visit to China is currently under way.
</P>
<P>
The China tour, scheduled to begin next Thursday, is expected
to forge more cooperation agreements and bring fresh momentum for
the Kazakh-Chinese ties, said Tokayev.
</P>
<P>
And a summit meeting of Kazakhstan, China, Russia, Kyrgyzstan
and Tajikistan here this summer will further the cooperative ties
among the five countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, he predicted, will be fruitful and beneficial to
the peace and stability of the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
