<HEADLINE> Sino-Norwegian Sewage Project Proceeds Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Norwegian "City and
Industrial Sewage Treatment Project" is proceeding smoothly in
Jiaxing, east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the two countries have jointly launched an
inspection of the city's water resources and have formulated a
detailed sewage treatment plan
</P>
<P>
Funding totalling 6.64 million Norwegian Krone (7.87 million
yuan) is helping the city solve deteriorating sewage problems and
improve the local environment.
</P>
<P>
Jiaxing has witnessed rapid economic development in recent
years, but has also suffered from wastewater pollution created by
local paper mills, dye mills and chemical plants.
</P>
<P>
Experts note the project will serve as a model for cities
with similar problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
