<DOCNO> XIE19980502.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ertan Hydropower Project Begins Water Storage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The dam of the Ertan Hydropower
Station located on the lower reaches of the Yalong River in
southwest China's Sichuan Province was locked on Friday to start
water storage.
</P>
<P>
In the following seven days, a 10-km-long river course starting
from the dam will have no water flow, and after that the sluice
gates will be lifted to let water flow in. By late June, the water
level of the reservoir is expected to get to 1,155 meters high,
which will enable electricity generating.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts conducted examinations last month on the
reservoir's preparation work for water storage, including
vegetation clearing and environmental protection. They agreed the
hydropower plant is ready for water storage.
</P>
<P>
A power generating unit with a capacity of 550,000 kw, the
first among the six in total, is now under installation and
tests. It is scheduled to generate electricity in July.
</P>
<P>
The Ertan Hydropower Project, built on the tributary of the
Yangtze River and near Panzhihua City, is the second largest of
its kind in China next to the Three Gorges Project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
