<HEADLINE> 17 Tamil Rebels killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 Tamil rebels were killed
by government troops on May 1 in Northern Province of the country,
military spokesman Rp Vitana said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Spokesman said around 12:15 p.m. Friday, government troops
confronted a group of Tamil rebels and engaged them with small
arms and mortars in a place southwest of Mankulam in Northern
province, killing at least nine rebels.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the troops sniped and killed two rebels in the same
day in a place southwest of Ampakaman, Vitana said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 12:30 p.m. Friday, government troops
killed four rebels in an ambush in the east of Ampakaman.
</P>
<P>
Government troops Friday also sniped and killed two terrorists
in Northwest of Olumadu, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the government
 for a separate state in the north and east of Sri Lanka since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
