<HEADLINE> Drought Hits Vietnam Electricity Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The English language weekly newspaper said an initial report
from Vietnamese electricity departments showed that the total
electricity shortage could climb to 250 million kwh this year.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in Vietnam's hydro-power plants are at record lows
due to the severe drought. This year's water flow into dams by
mid-April was only 69 percent of last year.
</P>
<P>
Forecasts say that if there is no rain by mid-May, water in
main reservoirs will fall to dead levels. 
</P>
