<HEADLINE> Leader Suggests High Albanian Cultural Autonomy for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The way out of the Kosovo crisis is
to give high cultural autonomy to Kosovo's ethnic Albanians,
Vojislav Seselj, the Serbian deputy prime minister and leader of
the Serbian Radical Party (SRP), said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav news agency Tanjug quoted Seselj as saying, when
interviewed by a Russian television station, that Kosovo ethnic
Albanians could have their own cultural autonomous bodies, but
couldn't establish their own government.
</P>
<P>
Seselj proposed that the Kosovo local authorities institute a
two-chamber system in order to prevent the Kosovo ethnic Albanians
having overwhelming majority in regional votes.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time for a senior Yugoslav leader to
publicly clarify his beliefs on solving the Kosovo issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
