<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Legislative Assembly Installed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Social Christian Unity Party
(PUSC) assumed its new role as the ruling party in Costa Rica when
the new legislative assembly for the 1998-2002 term was installed
Friday.
</P>
<P>
President-elect of the Republic Miguel Angel Rodriguez, also a
PUSC member, will be sworn in on May 8, replacing outgoing
President Jose Maria Figueres.
</P>
<P>
The PUSC won 27 deputy seats in the February 1 elections, two
less than the absolute majority in an assembly of 57
parliamentarians.
</P>
<P>
The National Liberation Party (PLN), of social democratic
leaning, lost the elections and power. Its parliamentary deputies
were reduced from 28 to only 23 in the present assembly. 
