<HEADLINE> Brunei Sultan to Visit Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Brunei Sultan Bolkiah is expected to
pay a working visit to Thailand in the middle of this month.
</P>
<P>
Thai Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan will travel to Brunei next
Monday to hand over an invitation letter of Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai to Brunei Sultan Bolkiah, the Thai Foreign Ministry was
quoted Saturday by the Nation as saying.
</P>
<P>
The letter will be handed over to Sultan Bolkiah Tuesday. Surin
will take the opportunity to meet with his counterpart Prince
Bolkiah the same day.
</P>
<P>
Brunei has given financial assistance of 500 million U.S.
dollars to help heal Thailand's economic crisis in the framework
of the International Monetary Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
