<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Colombia Guerrilla Attacks Kill 26 in a Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Guerrillas and
paramilitary groups killed 26 people in several attacks this week
in Colombia, official sources announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, alleged paramilitary groups attacked a district in
Urrao Municipality in Antioguia department, killing at least 21.
</P>
<P>
Another eight people were kidnapped Monday in the village of
Bello, also in Antioguia, and three of them were found dead on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that also on Monday there were three bomb
attacks on the offices of presidential candidates in Santafe de
Bogota. One person was killed in the attacks.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, suspected guerrillas of the National Liberation
Army (ELN) killed a 15-year-old boy in Barrancabermeja, in
Santander Department.
</P>
<P>
They also burned 15 buses in Medellin, the capital of
Antioquia, causing material losses of about 300,000
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
