<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Dutch Joint Venture Completes Second Phase Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of Huafei
Color Display System Co. Ltd., a Sino-Dutch joint venture,
entered production Thursday in Nanjing, capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the second phase project enables the joint
venture to produce six million color picture tubes and color
display tubes annually, The new production capacity ranks the
company as leading production center of color picture tubes and
color display tubes in Asia and Pacific regions.
</P>
<P>
Huafei Color Display System Co. Ltd. was jointly established
in 1986 by the International Trust and Investment Corporation of
Jiangsu Province, Nanjing-based Huadong Electronic Group and
Huadong Electronic Co. Ltd., and Philips of the Netherlands at an
investment of 460 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture has produced more than 10 million color
picture tubes since its operation in 1991. The venture's first
phase construction was completed at a cost of 180 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
An additional investment of 280 million US dollars was used
for second phase construction which was carried out over a two
year period. The facility features two imported production lines
for large-screen super horizontal color picture tubes, two
production lines for high definition color display tubes and
related auxiliary equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
