<HEADLINE> Romania Win Team Title in European Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Romania scored a comfortable win in
the women's team competition at the European Artistic Gymnastics
Championships in St. Petersburg, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Romanians, led by Simona Amanar, beat host nation Russia by
more than three points, 115.939 to 112.720, over the four
rotations.
</P>
<P>
The Russians managed to take the silver by edging out Ukraine,
who finished on 112.632. France were fourth with 112.277.
</P>
