<HEADLINE> Dow Approaches Record Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 1 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks rallied again and
charged back toward record levels Friday as investors believed that
interest rates will hold steady at more friendly economic data.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 83.70 points to 9,147.07.
The Dow gained nearly 200 points in two days and less than 40
points shy of last Tuesday's closing record of 9,184.94.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues led decliners by an 8-to-5 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 571.84 million shares as
against 693.06 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 9.26 to 1,121.01, the
Nasdaq composite index rose 5.03 to 1,873.44, and the NYSE
composite index rose 4.53 to 581.90.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.05 to
484.94, and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 3.34
to 749.86.,
</P>
<P>
The market was supported today by a series of reports on
manufacturing, construction, and personal income and spending
reinforced arguments that the economy isn't growing at an
inflationary pace.
</P>
<P>
Stocks tumbled on Monday on fears of an interest rate hike,
but the blue-chip index recovered all the lost ground after more
government data were revealed in the following days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
